Women in Investment Awards 2026 - Entry Questionnaire
International Investment Woman of the Year
Nadeeha A, HSBC Asset Management
Q1: Can you tell us about yourself and your journey to get where you are today? (max 150 words)
I grew up in India with a deep curiosity for how technology could solve real problems. I started my career at a mid-scale technology firm before joining KPMG as a data scientist, where I worked on automating systems for a major American bank using NLP models for document extraction. That experience opened my eyes to how AI could transform financial services at scale, and I knew I wanted to be closer to the investment side of the industry where these technologies could have the most impact. I joined HSBC's Data and Analytics Office in 2023 and quickly moved into the Asset Management investment value stream, where I now serve as Associate Data Science Lead. Getting here meant navigating a path that very few women from India take, building credibility in rooms where data science and investment management intersect, and constantly proving that technical innovation belongs at the heart of investment decision-making.
