Q2: How have you excelled in your current role, particularly over the past 12 months? (max 175 words)
My role sits at the intersection of data science and investment strategy, and over the past year I have focused on bringing genuinely transformative AI capabilities into HSBC Asset Management's investment processes. Working in close partnership with the Innovation and Quant Lab under the Chief Investment Office, I developed the data science and GenAI engine behind the QuantThematics project, which builds proprietary thematic investment signals that are replacing the firm's reliance on third-party ETFs. I have also delivered ESG analytics that senior decision-makers used to refine HSBC AM's proprietary ESG scoring methodology, and built regulatory dashboards now central to the firm's sustainability compliance. But what motivates me most is making sure I am not the only one who understands this technology. I have trained over 150 colleagues across Asset Management and Wealth and Premier Banking in AI and prompt engineering, mentored interns who have since converted to full-time data scientists, and captained a group-wide Coaching Circle focused on wellbeing and peer support.
[Word count: 166]
Q3: What have been your big achievements in the past 12 months and why should you win this award this year? What impact have you made? (max 250 words)
My biggest achievement this year has been helping HSBC Asset Management move from talking about AI to actually using it in live investment processes. The QuantThematics project I contributed to is now building 8+ internal thematic universes across themes like Water, Defence, Climate, and Biodiversity, with an estimated commercial impact of $8.4M to $16.4M through savings in client fees ($2.7M), FTE costs ($100k annually), and data licensing. This work directly supports the firm's strategy to build proprietary investment products and contribute to Discretionary Portfolio Management targeting $100bn+ in AUM by 2029.
Beyond this, I automated Financed Carbon Emissions calculations supporting HSBC AM's commitment to reduce portfolio emissions by 58% by 2030, built Policy and ESMA Dashboards that are now core to the firm's regulatory compliance and risk oversight, and delivered proof-of-concept GenAI solutions for ESG due diligence scoring and social opportunity fund analysis.
Outside my day job, I placed 5th globally in the coding category at the Global Prompt Engineering Championship in Dubai, the only Indian representative in my category among 3,400 entries. I brought that expertise back into HSBC, training over 150 colleagues in AI literacy and prompt engineering across two business divisions. I mentored interns through to full-time conversion, captained a group-wide Coaching Circle for mental wellbeing, and co-developed a GenAI-powered TCFD Reporting Tool that reached the final 27 teams across the entire HSBC Group at the NOVA Hackathon.
I believe I should win because I represent what the future of the investment industry looks like: someone who builds the technology, teaches others to use it, and creates a culture where innovation and inclusion go hand in hand.
